60/* Format of the configuration file:
61
62 # Configuration data is parsed as follows:
63 # 1. command line options
64 # 2. user-specific file
65 # 3. system-wide file
66 # Any configuration value is only changed the first time it is set.
67 # Thus, host-specific definitions should be at the beginning of the
68 # configuration file, and defaults at the end.
69
70 # Host-specific declarations. These may override anything above. A single
71 # host may match multiple declarations; these are processed in the order
72 # that they are given in.
73
74 Host *.ngs.fi ngs.fi
75 User foo
76
77 Host fake.com
78 HostName another.host.name.real.org
79 User blaah
80 Port 34289
81 ForwardX11 no
82 ForwardAgent no
83
84 Host books.com
85 RemoteForward 9999 shadows.cs.hut.fi:9999
86 Ciphers 3des-cbc
87
88 Host fascist.blob.com
89 Port 23123
90 User tylonen
91 PasswordAuthentication no
92
93 Host puukko.hut.fi
94 User t35124p
95 ProxyCommand ssh-proxy %h %p
96
97 Host *.fr
98 PublicKeyAuthentication no
99
100 Host *.su
101 Ciphers aes128-ctr
102 PasswordAuthentication no
103
104 Host vpn.fake.com
105 Tunnel yes
106 TunnelDevice 3
107
108 # Defaults for various options
109 Host *
110 ForwardAgent no
111 ForwardX11 no
112 PasswordAuthentication yes
113 RSAAuthentication yes
114 RhostsRSAAuthentication yes
115 StrictHostKeyChecking yes
116 TcpKeepAlive no
117 IdentityFile ~/.ssh/identity
118 Port 22
119 EscapeChar ~
120
121*/

343/*
344 * Adds a local TCP/IP port forward to options. Never returns if there is an
345 * error.
346 */
347
348void
349add_local_forward(Options *options, const struct Forward *newfwd)
350{
351 struct Forward *fwd;
352 int i;
353
354 /* Don't add duplicates */
355 for (i = 0; i < options->num_local_forwards; i++) {
356 if (forward_equals(newfwd, options->local_forwards + i))
357 return;
358 }
359 options->local_forwards = xreallocarray(options->local_forwards,
360 options->num_local_forwards + 1,
361 sizeof(*options->local_forwards));
362 fwd = &options->local_forwards[options->num_local_forwards++];
363
364 fwd->listen_host = newfwd->listen_host;
365 fwd->listen_port = newfwd->listen_port;
366 fwd->listen_path = newfwd->listen_path;
367 fwd->connect_host = newfwd->connect_host;
368 fwd->connect_port = newfwd->connect_port;
369 fwd->connect_path = newfwd->connect_path;
370}

377void
378add_remote_forward(Options *options, const struct Forward *newfwd)
379{
380 struct Forward *fwd;
381 int i;
382
383 /* Don't add duplicates */
384 for (i = 0; i < options->num_remote_forwards; i++) {
385 if (forward_equals(newfwd, options->remote_forwards + i))
386 return;
387 }
388 options->remote_forwards = xreallocarray(options->remote_forwards,
389 options->num_remote_forwards + 1,
390 sizeof(*options->remote_forwards));
391 fwd = &options->remote_forwards[options->num_remote_forwards++];
392
393 fwd->listen_host = newfwd->listen_host;
394 fwd->listen_port = newfwd->listen_port;
395 fwd->listen_path = newfwd->listen_path;
396 fwd->connect_host = newfwd->connect_host;
397 fwd->connect_port = newfwd->connect_port;
398 fwd->connect_path = newfwd->connect_path;
399 fwd->handle = newfwd->handle;
400 fwd->allocated_port = 0;
401}

403static void
404clear_forwardings(Options *options)
405{
406 int i;
407
408 for (i = 0; i < options->num_local_forwards; i++) {
409 free(options->local_forwards[i].listen_host);
410 free(options->local_forwards[i].listen_path);
411 free(options->local_forwards[i].connect_host);
412 free(options->local_forwards[i].connect_path);
413 }
414 if (options->num_local_forwards > 0) {
415 free(options->local_forwards);
416 options->local_forwards = NULL;
417 }
418 options->num_local_forwards = 0;
419 for (i = 0; i < options->num_remote_forwards; i++) {
420 free(options->remote_forwards[i].listen_host);
421 free(options->remote_forwards[i].listen_path);
422 free(options->remote_forwards[i].connect_host);
423 free(options->remote_forwards[i].connect_path);
424 }
425 if (options->num_remote_forwards > 0) {
426 free(options->remote_forwards);
427 options->remote_forwards = NULL;
428 }
429 options->num_remote_forwards = 0;
430 options->tun_open = SSH_TUNMODE_NO;
431}

433void
434add_certificate_file(Options *options, const char *path, int userprovided)
435{
436 int i;
437
438 if (options->num_certificate_files >= SSH_MAX_CERTIFICATE_FILES)
439 fatal("Too many certificate files specified (max %d)",
440 SSH_MAX_CERTIFICATE_FILES);
441
442 /* Avoid registering duplicates */
443 for (i = 0; i < options->num_certificate_files; i++) {
444 if (options->certificate_file_userprovided[i] == userprovided &&
445 strcmp(options->certificate_files[i], path) == 0) {
446 debug2("%s: ignoring duplicate key %s", __func__, path);
447 return;
448 }
449 }
450
451 options->certificate_file_userprovided[options->num_certificate_files] =
452 userprovided;
453 options->certificate_files[options->num_certificate_files++] =
454 xstrdup(path);
455}

457void
458add_identity_file(Options *options, const char *dir, const char *filename,
459 int userprovided)
460{
461 char *path;
462 int i;
463
464 if (options->num_identity_files >= SSH_MAX_IDENTITY_FILES)
465 fatal("Too many identity files specified (max %d)",
466 SSH_MAX_IDENTITY_FILES);
467
468 if (dir == NULL) /* no dir, filename is absolute */
469 path = xstrdup(filename);
470 else if (xasprintf(&path, "%s%s", dir, filename) >= PATH_MAX)
471 fatal("Identity file path %s too long", path);
472
473 /* Avoid registering duplicates */
474 for (i = 0; i < options->num_identity_files; i++) {
475 if (options->identity_file_userprovided[i] == userprovided &&
476 strcmp(options->identity_files[i], path) == 0) {
477 debug2("%s: ignoring duplicate key %s", __func__, path);
478 free(path);
479 return;
480 }
481 }
482
483 options->identity_file_userprovided[options->num_identity_files] =
484 userprovided;
485 options->identity_files[options->num_identity_files++] = path;
486}

488int
489default_ssh_port(void)
490{
491 static int port;
492 struct servent *sp;
493
494 if (port == 0) {
495 sp = getservbyname(SSH_SERVICE_NAME, "tcp");
496 port = sp ? ntohs(sp->s_port) : SSH_DEFAULT_PORT;
497 }
498 return port;
499}

501/*
502 * Execute a command in a shell.
503 * Return its exit status or -1 on abnormal exit.
504 */
505static int
506execute_in_shell(const char *cmd)
507{
508 const char *shell;
509 pid_t pid;
510 int devnull, status;
511
512 if ((shell = getenv("SHELL")) == NULL)
513 shell = _PATH_BSHELL;
514
515 /* Need this to redirect subprocess stdin/out */
516 if ((devnull = open(_PATH_DEVNULL, O_RDWR)) == -1)
517 fatal("open(/dev/null): %s", strerror(errno));
518
519 debug("Executing command: '%.500s'", cmd);
520
521 /* Fork and execute the command. */
522 if ((pid = fork()) == 0) {
523 char *argv[4];
524
525 /* Redirect child stdin and stdout. Leave stderr */
526 if (dup2(devnull, STDIN_FILENO) == -1)
527 fatal("dup2: %s", strerror(errno));
528 if (dup2(devnull, STDOUT_FILENO) == -1)
529 fatal("dup2: %s", strerror(errno));
530 if (devnull > STDERR_FILENO)
531 close(devnull);
532 if (closefrom(STDERR_FILENO + 1) == -1)
533 fatal("closefrom: %s", strerror(errno));
534
535 argv[0] = __UNCONST(shell);
536 argv[1] = __UNCONST("-c");
537 argv[2] = xstrdup(cmd);
538 argv[3] = NULL;
539
540 execv(argv[0], argv);
541 error("Unable to execute '%.100s': %s", cmd, strerror(errno));
542 /* Die with signal to make this error apparent to parent. */
543 signal(SIGTERM, SIG_DFL);
544 kill(getpid(), SIGTERM);
545 _exit(1);
546 }
547 /* Parent. */
548 if (pid < 0)
549 fatal("%s: fork: %.100s", __func__, strerror(errno));
550
551 close(devnull);
552
553 while (waitpid(pid, &status, 0) == -1) {
554 if (errno != EINTR && errno != EAGAIN)
555 fatal("%s: waitpid: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
556 }
557 if (!WIFEXITED(status)) {
558 error("command '%.100s' exited abnormally", cmd);
559 return -1;
560 }
561 debug3("command returned status %d", WEXITSTATUS(status));
562 return WEXITSTATUS(status);
563}

565/*
566 * Parse and execute a Match directive.
567 */
568static int
569match_cfg_line(Options *options, char **condition, struct passwd *pw,
570 const char *host_arg, const char *original_host, int final_pass,
571 int *want_final_pass, const char *filename, int linenum)
572{
573 char *arg, *oattrib, *attrib, *cmd, *cp = *condition, *host, *criteria;
574 const char *ruser;
575 int r, port, this_result, result = 1, attributes = 0, negate;
576 char thishost[NI_MAXHOST], shorthost[NI_MAXHOST], portstr[NI_MAXSERV];
577 char uidstr[32];
578
579 /*
580 * Configuration is likely to be incomplete at this point so we
581 * must be prepared to use default values.
582 */
583 port = options->port <= 0 ? default_ssh_port() : options->port;
584 ruser = options->user == NULL ? pw->pw_name : options->user;
585 if (final_pass) {
586 host = xstrdup(options->hostname);
587 } else if (options->hostname != NULL) {
588 /* NB. Please keep in sync with ssh.c:main() */
589 host = percent_expand(options->hostname,
590 "h", host_arg, (char *)NULL);
591 } else {
592 host = xstrdup(host_arg);
593 }
594
595 debug2("checking match for '%s' host %s originally %s",
596 cp, host, original_host);
597 while ((oattrib = attrib = strdelim(&cp)) && *attrib != '\0') {
598 criteria = NULL;
599 this_result = 1;
600 if ((negate = attrib[0] == '!'))
601 attrib++;
602 /* criteria "all" and "canonical" have no argument */
603 if (strcasecmp(attrib, "all") == 0) {
604 if (attributes > 1 ||
605 ((arg = strdelim(&cp)) != NULL && *arg != '\0')) {
606 error("%.200s line %d: '%s' cannot be combined "
607 "with other Match attributes",
608 filename, linenum, oattrib);
609 result = -1;
610 goto out;
611 }
612 if (result)
613 result = negate ? 0 : 1;
614 goto out;
615 }
616 attributes++;
617 if (strcasecmp(attrib, "canonical") == 0 ||
618 strcasecmp(attrib, "final") == 0) {
619 /*
620 * If the config requests "Match final" then remember
621 * this so we can perform a second pass later.
622 */
623 if (strcasecmp(attrib, "final") == 0 &&
624 want_final_pass != NULL)
625 *want_final_pass = 1;
626 r = !!final_pass; /* force bitmask member to boolean */
627 if (r == (negate ? 1 : 0))
628 this_result = result = 0;
629 debug3("%.200s line %d: %smatched '%s'",
630 filename, linenum,
631 this_result ? "" : "not ", oattrib);
632 continue;
633 }
634 /* All other criteria require an argument */
635 if ((arg = strdelim(&cp)) == NULL || *arg == '\0') {
636 error("Missing Match criteria for %s", attrib);
637 result = -1;
638 goto out;
639 }
640 if (strcasecmp(attrib, "host") == 0) {
641 criteria = xstrdup(host);
642 r = match_hostname(host, arg) == 1;
643 if (r == (negate ? 1 : 0))
644 this_result = result = 0;
645 } else if (strcasecmp(attrib, "originalhost") == 0) {
646 criteria = xstrdup(original_host);
647 r = match_hostname(original_host, arg) == 1;
648 if (r == (negate ? 1 : 0))
649 this_result = result = 0;
650 } else if (strcasecmp(attrib, "user") == 0) {
651 criteria = xstrdup(ruser);
652 r = match_pattern_list(ruser, arg, 0) == 1;
653 if (r == (negate ? 1 : 0))
654 this_result = result = 0;
655 } else if (strcasecmp(attrib, "localuser") == 0) {
656 criteria = xstrdup(pw->pw_name);
657 r = match_pattern_list(pw->pw_name, arg, 0) == 1;
658 if (r == (negate ? 1 : 0))
659 this_result = result = 0;
660 } else if (strcasecmp(attrib, "exec") == 0) {
661 if (gethostname(thishost, sizeof(thishost)) == -1)
662 fatal("gethostname: %s", strerror(errno));
663 strlcpy(shorthost, thishost, sizeof(shorthost));
664 shorthost[strcspn(thishost, ".")] = '\0';
665 snprintf(portstr, sizeof(portstr), "%d", port);
666 snprintf(uidstr, sizeof(uidstr), "%llu",
667 (unsigned long long)pw->pw_uid);
668
669 cmd = percent_expand(arg,
670 "L", shorthost,
671 "d", pw->pw_dir,
672 "h", host,
673 "l", thishost,
674 "n", original_host,
675 "p", portstr,
676 "r", ruser,
677 "u", pw->pw_name,
678 "i", uidstr,
679 (char *)NULL);
680 if (result != 1) {
681 /* skip execution if prior predicate failed */
682 debug3("%.200s line %d: skipped exec "
683 "\"%.100s\"", filename, linenum, cmd);
684 free(cmd);
685 continue;
686 }
687 r = execute_in_shell(cmd);
688 if (r == -1) {
689 fatal("%.200s line %d: match exec "
690 "'%.100s' error", filename,
691 linenum, cmd);
692 }
693 criteria = xstrdup(cmd);
694 free(cmd);
695 /* Force exit status to boolean */
696 r = r == 0;
697 if (r == (negate ? 1 : 0))
698 this_result = result = 0;
699 } else {
700 error("Unsupported Match attribute %s", attrib);
701 result = -1;
702 goto out;
703 }
704 debug3("%.200s line %d: %smatched '%s \"%.100s\"' ",
705 filename, linenum, this_result ? "": "not ",
706 oattrib, criteria);
707 free(criteria);
708 }
709 if (attributes == 0) {
710 error("One or more attributes required for Match");
711 result = -1;
712 goto out;
713 }
714 out:
715 if (result != -1)
716 debug2("match %sfound", result ? "" : "not ");
717 *condition = cp;
718 free(host);
719 return result;
720}

722/* Remove environment variable by pattern */
723static void
724rm_env(Options *options, const char *arg, const char *filename, int linenum)
725{
726 int i, j;
727 char *cp;
728
729 /* Remove an environment variable */
730 for (i = 0; i < options->num_send_env; ) {
731 cp = xstrdup(options->send_env[i]);
732 if (!match_pattern(cp, arg + 1)) {
733 free(cp);
734 i++;
735 continue;
736 }
737 debug3("%s line %d: removing environment %s",
738 filename, linenum, cp);
739 free(cp);
740 free(options->send_env[i]);
741 options->send_env[i] = NULL;
742 for (j = i; j < options->num_send_env - 1; j++) {
743 options->send_env[j] = options->send_env[j + 1];
744 options->send_env[j + 1] = NULL;
745 }
746 options->num_send_env--;
747 /* NB. don't increment i */
748 }
749}

751/*
752 * Returns the number of the token pointed to by cp or oBadOption.
753 */
754static OpCodes
755parse_token(const char *cp, const char *filename, int linenum,
756 const char *ignored_unknown)
757{
758 int i;
759
760 for (i = 0; keywords[i].name; i++)
761 if (strcmp(cp, keywords[i].name) == 0)
762 return keywords[i].opcode;
763 if (ignored_unknown != NULL &&
764 match_pattern_list(cp, ignored_unknown, 1) == 1)
765 return oIgnoredUnknownOption;
766 error("%s: line %d: Bad configuration option: %s",
767 filename, linenum, cp);
768 return oBadOption;
769}

854 * Processes a single option line as used in the configuration files. This
855 * only sets those values that have not already been set.
856 */
857int
858process_config_line(Options *options, struct passwd *pw, const char *host,
859 const char *original_host, char *line, const char *filename,
860 int linenum, int *activep, int flags)
861{
862 return process_config_line_depth(options, pw, host, original_host,
863 line, filename, linenum, activep, flags, NULL, 0);
864}

873 char **cpptr, fwdarg[256];

875 int r, oactive, negated, opcode, *intptr, value, value2, cmdline = 0;
876 int remotefwd, dynamicfwd;

888 cmdline = 1;

890 }

892 /* Strip trailing whitespace. Allow \f (form feed) at EOL only */
893 if ((len = strlen(line)) == 0)
894 return 0;

896 if (strchr(WHITESPACE "\f", line[len]) == NULL)
897 break;

905 /* Ignore leading whitespace. */

1359 if (!dynamicfwd) {
1360 arg2 = strdelim(&s);
1361 if (arg2 == NULL || *arg2 == '\0') {
1362 if (remotefwd)
1363 dynamicfwd = 1;
1364 else
1365 fatal("%.200s line %d: Missing target "
1366 "argument.", filename, linenum);
1367 } else {
1368 /* construct a string for parse_forward */
1369 snprintf(fwdarg, sizeof(fwdarg), "%s:%s", arg,
1370 arg2);
1371 }
1372 }
1373 if (dynamicfwd)
1374 strlcpy(fwdarg, arg, sizeof(fwdarg));
1375
1376 if (parse_forward(&fwd, fwdarg, dynamicfwd, remotefwd) == 0)
1377 fatal("%.200s line %d: Bad forwarding specification.",
1378 filename, linenum);
1379
1380 if (*activep) {
1381 if (remotefwd) {
1382 add_remote_forward(options, &fwd);
1383 } else {
1384 add_local_forward(options, &fwd);
1385 }
1386 }
1387 break;
1388
1389 case oClearAllForwardings:
1390 intptr = &options->clear_forwardings;
1391 goto parse_flag;
1392
1393 case oHost:
1394 if (cmdline)
1395 fatal("Host directive not supported as a command-line "
1396 "option");
1397 *activep = 0;
1398 arg2 = NULL;
1399 while ((arg = strdelim(&s)) != NULL && *arg != '\0') {
1400 if ((flags & SSHCONF_NEVERMATCH) != 0)
1401 break;
1402 negated = *arg == '!';
1403 if (negated)
1404 arg++;
1405 if (match_pattern(host, arg)) {
1406 if (negated) {
1407 debug("%.200s line %d: Skipping Host "
1408 "block because of negated match "
1409 "for %.100s", filename, linenum,
1410 arg);
1411 *activep = 0;
1412 break;
1413 }
1414 if (!*activep)
1415 arg2 = arg; /* logged below */
1416 *activep = 1;
1417 }
1418 }
1419 if (*activep)
1420 debug("%.200s line %d: Applying options for %.100s",
1421 filename, linenum, arg2);
1422 /* Avoid garbage check below, as strdelim is done. */
1423 return 0;
1424
1425 case oMatch:
1426 if (cmdline)
1427 fatal("Host directive not supported as a command-line "
1428 "option");
1429 value = match_cfg_line(options, &s, pw, host, original_host,
1430 flags & SSHCONF_FINAL, want_final_pass,
1431 filename, linenum);
1432 if (value < 0)
1433 fatal("%.200s line %d: Bad Match condition", filename,
1434 linenum);
1435 *activep = (flags & SSHCONF_NEVERMATCH) ? 0 : value;
1436 break;
1437
1438 case oEscapeChar:
1439 intptr = &options->escape_char;
1440 arg = strdelim(&s);
1441 if (!arg || *arg == '\0')
1442 fatal("%.200s line %d: Missing argument.", filename, linenum);
1443 value = 0; /* To avoid compiler warning... */
1444 if (strcmp(arg, "none") == 0)
1445 value = SSH_ESCAPECHAR_NONE;
1446 else if (arg[1] == '\0')
1447 value = (u_char) arg[0];
1448 else if (arg[0] == '^' && arg[2] == 0 &&
1449 (u_char) arg[1] >= 64 && (u_char) arg[1] < 128)
1450 value = (u_char) arg[1] & 31;
1451 else {
1452 fatal("%.200s line %d: Bad escape character.",
1453 filename, linenum);
1454 /* NOTREACHED */
1455 value = 0; /* Avoid compiler warning. */
1456 }
1457 if (*activep && *intptr == -1)
1458 *intptr = value;
1459 break;
1460
1461 case oAddressFamily:
1462 intptr = &options->address_family;
1463 multistate_ptr = multistate_addressfamily;
1464 goto parse_multistate;
1465
1466 case oEnableSSHKeysign:
1467 intptr = &options->enable_ssh_keysign;
1468 goto parse_flag;
1469
1470 case oIdentitiesOnly:
1471 intptr = &options->identities_only;
1472 goto parse_flag;
1473
1474 case oServerAliveInterval:
1475 intptr = &options->server_alive_interval;
1476 goto parse_time;
1477
1478 case oServerAliveCountMax:

1480 goto parse_int;
1481
1482 case oSendEnv:
1483 while ((arg = strdelim(&s)) != NULL && *arg != '\0') {
1484 if (strchr(arg, '=') != NULL)
1485 fatal("%s line %d: Invalid environment name.",
1486 filename, linenum);
1487 if (!*activep)
1488 continue;
1489 if (*arg == '-') {
1490 /* Removing an env var */
1491 rm_env(options, arg, filename, linenum);
1492 continue;
1493 } else {
1494 /* Adding an env var */
1495 if (options->num_send_env >= INT_MAX)
1496 fatal("%s line %d: too many send env.",
1497 filename, linenum);
1498 options->send_env = xrecallocarray(
1499 options->send_env, options->num_send_env,
1500 options->num_send_env + 1,
1501 sizeof(*options->send_env));
1502 options->send_env[options->num_send_env++] =
1503 xstrdup(arg);
1504 }
1505 }
1506 break;
1507
1508 case oSetEnv:
1509 value = options->num_setenv;
1510 while ((arg = strdelimw(&s)) != NULL && *arg != '\0') {
1511 if (strchr(arg, '=') == NULL)
1512 fatal("%s line %d: Invalid SetEnv.",
1513 filename, linenum);
1514 if (!*activep || value != 0)
1515 continue;
1516 /* Adding a setenv var */
1517 if (options->num_setenv >= INT_MAX)
1518 fatal("%s line %d: too many SetEnv.",
1519 filename, linenum);
1520 options->setenv = xrecallocarray(
1521 options->setenv, options->num_setenv,
1522 options->num_setenv + 1, sizeof(*options->setenv));
1523 options->setenv[options->num_setenv++] = xstrdup(arg);
1524 }
1525 break;
1526
1527 case oControlPath:
1528 charptr = &options->control_path;
1529 goto parse_string;
1530
1531 case oControlMaster:

1533 multistate_ptr = multistate_controlmaster;
1534 goto parse_multistate;
1535
1536 case oControlPersist:
1537 /* no/false/yes/true, or a time spec */
1538 intptr = &options->control_persist;
1539 arg = strdelim(&s);
1540 if (!arg || *arg == '\0')
1541 fatal("%.200s line %d: Missing ControlPersist"
1542 " argument.", filename, linenum);
1543 value = 0;
1544 value2 = 0; /* timeout */

1546 value = 0;
1547 else if (strcmp(arg, "yes") == 0 || strcmp(arg, "true") == 0)
1548 value = 1;
1549 else if ((value2 = convtime(arg)) >= 0)
1550 value = 1;
1551 else
1552 fatal("%.200s line %d: Bad ControlPersist argument.",
1553 filename, linenum);
1554 if (*activep && *intptr == -1) {
1555 *intptr = value;
1556 options->control_persist_timeout = value2;
1557 }
1558 break;

1560 case oHashKnownHosts:
1561 intptr = &options->hash_known_hosts;
1562 goto parse_flag;

1564 case oTunnel:

1566 multistate_ptr = multistate_tunnel;
1567 goto parse_multistate;

1569 case oTunnelDevice:
1570 arg = strdelim(&s);
1571 if (!arg || *arg == '\0')
1572 fatal("%.200s line %d: Missing argument.", filename, linenum);
1573 value = a2tun(arg, &value2);

1577 options->tun_local = value;
1578 options->tun_remote = value2;

1583 charptr = &options->local_command;
1584 goto parse_command;
1585
1586 case oPermitLocalCommand:
1587 intptr = &options->permit_local_command;
1588 goto parse_flag;

1591 charptr = &options->remote_command;
1592 goto parse_command;

1594 case oVisualHostKey:

1596 goto parse_flag;
1597
1598 case oInclude:
1599 if (cmdline)
1600 fatal("Include directive not supported as a "
1601 "command-line option");
1602 value = 0;
1603 while ((arg = strdelim(&s)) != NULL && *arg != '\0') {
1604 /*
1605 * Ensure all paths are anchored. User configuration
1606 * files may begin with '~/' but system configurations
1607 * must not. If the path is relative, then treat it
1608 * as living in ~/.ssh for user configurations or
1609 * /etc/ssh for system ones.
1610 */
1611 if (*arg == '~' && (flags & SSHCONF_USERCONF) == 0)
1612 fatal("%.200s line %d: bad include path %s.",
1613 filename, linenum, arg);
1614 if (!path_absolute(arg) && *arg != '~') {
1615 xasprintf(&arg2, "%s/%s",
1616 (flags & SSHCONF_USERCONF) ?
1617 "~/" _PATH_SSH_USER_DIR : SSHDIR, arg);
1618 } else
1619 arg2 = xstrdup(arg);
1620 memset(&gl, 0, sizeof(gl));
1621 r = glob(arg2, GLOB_TILDE | GLOB_LIMIT, NULL, &gl);
1622 if (r == GLOB_NOMATCH) {
1623 debug("%.200s line %d: include %s matched no "
1624 "files",filename, linenum, arg2);
1625 free(arg2);
1626 continue;
1627 } else if (r != 0)
1628 fatal("%.200s line %d: glob failed for %s.",
1629 filename, linenum, arg2);
1630 free(arg2);
1631 oactive = *activep;
1632 for (i = 0; i < (u_int)gl.gl_pathc; i++) {
1633 debug3("%.200s line %d: Including file %s "
1634 "depth %d%s", filename, linenum,
1635 gl.gl_pathv[i], depth,
1636 oactive ? "" : " (parse only)");
1637 r = read_config_file_depth(gl.gl_pathv[i],
1638 pw, host, original_host, options,
1639 flags | SSHCONF_CHECKPERM |
1640 (oactive ? 0 : SSHCONF_NEVERMATCH),
1641 activep, want_final_pass, depth + 1);
1642 if (r != 1 && errno != ENOENT) {
1643 fatal("Can't open user config file "
1644 "%.100s: %.100s", gl.gl_pathv[i],
1645 strerror(errno));
1646 }
1647 /*
1648 * don't let Match in includes clobber the
1649 * containing file's Match state.
1650 */
1651 *activep = oactive;
1652 if (r != 1)
1653 value = -1;
1654 }
1655 globfree(&gl);
1656 }
1657 if (value != 0)
1658 return value;
1659 break;
1660
1661 case oIPQoS:
1662 arg = strdelim(&s);
1663 if ((value = parse_ipqos(arg)) == -1)
1664 fatal("%s line %d: Bad IPQoS value: %s",
1665 filename, linenum, arg);
1666 arg = strdelim(&s);
1667 if (arg == NULL)
1668 value2 = value;
1669 else if ((value2 = parse_ipqos(arg)) == -1)
1670 fatal("%s line %d: Bad IPQoS value: %s",
1671 filename, linenum, arg);
1672 if (*activep) {
1673 options->ip_qos_interactive = value;
1674 options->ip_qos_bulk = value2;
1675 }
1676 break;

1678 case oRequestTTY:
1679 intptr = &options->request_tty;
1680 multistate_ptr = multistate_requesttty;
1681 goto parse_multistate;
1682
1683 case oSendVersionFirst:
1684 intptr = &options->send_version_first;
1685 goto parse_flag;
1686
1687 case oIgnoreUnknown:
1688 charptr = &options->ignored_unknown;
1689 goto parse_string;
1690
1691 case oProxyUseFdpass:
1692 intptr = &options->proxy_use_fdpass;
1693 goto parse_flag;
1694
1695 case oCanonicalDomains:
1696 value = options->num_canonical_domains != 0;
1697 while ((arg = strdelim(&s)) != NULL && *arg != '\0') {
1698 if (!valid_domain(arg, 1, &errstr)) {
1699 fatal("%s line %d: %s", filename, linenum,
1700 errstr);
1701 }
1702 if (!*activep || value)
1703 continue;
1704 if (options->num_canonical_domains >= MAX_CANON_DOMAINS)
1705 fatal("%s line %d: too many hostname suffixes.",
1706 filename, linenum);
1707 options->canonical_domains[
1708 options->num_canonical_domains++] = xstrdup(arg);
1709 }
1710 break;
1711
1712 case oCanonicalizePermittedCNAMEs:
1713 value = options->num_permitted_cnames != 0;
1714 while ((arg = strdelim(&s)) != NULL && *arg != '\0') {
1715 /* Either '*' for everything or 'list:list' */
1716 if (strcmp(arg, "*") == 0)
1717 arg2 = arg;
1718 else {
1719 lowercase(arg);
1720 if ((arg2 = strchr(arg, ':')) == NULL ||
1721 arg2[1] == '\0') {
1722 fatal("%s line %d: "
1723 "Invalid permitted CNAME \"%s\"",
1724 filename, linenum, arg);
1725 }
1726 *arg2 = '\0';
1727 arg2++;
1728 }
1729 if (!*activep || value)
1730 continue;
1731 if (options->num_permitted_cnames >= MAX_CANON_DOMAINS)
1732 fatal("%s line %d: too many permitted CNAMEs.",
1733 filename, linenum);
1734 cname = options->permitted_cnames +
1735 options->num_permitted_cnames++;
1736 cname->source_list = xstrdup(arg);
1737 cname->target_list = xstrdup(arg2);
1738 }
1739 break;
1740
1741 case oCanonicalizeHostname:
1742 intptr = &options->canonicalize_hostname;
1743 multistate_ptr = multistate_canonicalizehostname;
1744 goto parse_multistate;
1745
1746 case oCanonicalizeMaxDots:
1747 intptr = &options->canonicalize_max_dots;
1748 goto parse_int;
1749
1750 case oCanonicalizeFallbackLocal:
1751 intptr = &options->canonicalize_fallback_local;
1752 goto parse_flag;

1769 case oRevokedHostKeys:

1771 goto parse_string;
1772
1773 case oFingerprintHash:
1774 intptr = &options->fingerprint_hash;

1778 filename, linenum);

1781 filename, linenum, arg);

1783 *intptr = value;
1784 break;
1785
1786 case oUpdateHostkeys:
1787 intptr = &options->update_hostkeys;
1788 multistate_ptr = multistate_yesnoask;
1789 goto parse_multistate;
1790
1791 case oHostbasedKeyTypes:
1792 charptr = &options->hostbased_key_types;
1793 goto parse_keytypes;
1794
1795 case oPubkeyAcceptedKeyTypes:
1796 charptr = &options->pubkey_key_types;
1797 goto parse_keytypes;
1798
1799 case oAddKeysToAgent:
1800 intptr = &options->add_keys_to_agent;

1802 goto parse_multistate;
1803
1804 case oIdentityAgent:
1805 charptr = &options->identity_agent;
1806 arg = strdelim(&s);
1807 if (!arg || *arg == '\0')
1808 fatal("%.200s line %d: Missing argument.",
1809 filename, linenum);
1810 /* Extra validation if the string represents an env var. */
1811 if (arg[0] == '$' && !valid_env_name(arg + 1)) {
1812 fatal("%.200s line %d: Invalid environment name %s.",
1813 filename, linenum, arg);
1814 }
1815 if (*activep && *charptr == NULL)
1816 *charptr = xstrdup(arg);
1817 break;
1818
1819 case oDeprecated:
1820 debug("%s line %d: Deprecated option \"%s\"",
1821 filename, linenum, keyword);
1822 return 0;
1823
1824 case oUnsupported:

1834 if ((arg = strdelim(&s)) != NULL && *arg != '\0') {
1835 fatal("%.200s line %d: garbage at end of line; \"%.200s\".",
1836 filename, linenum, arg);
1837 }
1838 return 0;
1839}

1841/*
1842 * Reads the config file and modifies the options accordingly. Options
1843 * should already be initialized before this call. This never returns if
1844 * there is an error. If the file does not exist, this returns 0.
1845 */
1846int
1847read_config_file(const char *filename, struct passwd *pw, const char *host,
1848 const char *original_host, Options *options, int flags,
1849 int *want_final_pass)
1850{
1851 int active = 1;
1852
1853 return read_config_file_depth(filename, pw, host, original_host,
1854 options, flags, &active, want_final_pass, 0);
1855}
1856
1857#define READCONF_MAX_DEPTH 16
1858static int
1859read_config_file_depth(const char *filename, struct passwd *pw,
1860 const char *host, const char *original_host, Options *options,
1861 int flags, int *activep, int *want_final_pass, int depth)
1862{
1863 FILE *f;
1864 char *line = NULL;
1865 size_t linesize = 0;
1866 int linenum;
1867 int bad_options = 0;
1868
1869 if (depth < 0 || depth > READCONF_MAX_DEPTH)
1870 fatal("Too many recursive configuration includes");
1871
1872 if ((f = fopen(filename, "r")) == NULL)
1873 return 0;
1874
1875 if (flags & SSHCONF_CHECKPERM) {
1876 struct stat sb;
1877
1878 if (fstat(fileno(f), &sb) == -1)
1879 fatal("fstat %s: %s", filename, strerror(errno));
1880 if (((sb.st_uid != 0 && sb.st_uid != getuid()) ||
1881 (sb.st_mode & 022) != 0))
1882 fatal("Bad owner or permissions on %s", filename);
1883 }
1884
1885 debug("Reading configuration data %.200s", filename);
1886
1887 /*
1888 * Mark that we are now processing the options. This flag is turned
1889 * on/off by Host specifications.
1890 */
1891 linenum = 0;
1892 while (getline(&line, &linesize, f) != -1) {
1893 /* Update line number counter. */
1894 linenum++;
1895 if (process_config_line_depth(options, pw, host, original_host,
1896 line, filename, linenum, activep, flags, want_final_pass,
1897 depth) != 0)
1898 bad_options++;
1899 }
1900 free(line);
1901 fclose(f);
1902 if (bad_options > 0)
1903 fatal("%s: terminating, %d bad configuration options",
1904 filename, bad_options);
1905 return 1;
1906}

1908/* Returns 1 if a string option is unset or set to "none" or 0 otherwise. */
1909int
1910option_clear_or_none(const char *o)
1911{
1912 return o == NULL || strcasecmp(o, "none") == 0;
1913}

2299struct fwdarg {
2300 char *arg;
2301 int ispath;
2302};

2304/*
2305 * parse_fwd_field
2306 * parses the next field in a port forwarding specification.
2307 * sets fwd to the parsed field and advances p past the colon
2308 * or sets it to NULL at end of string.
2309 * returns 0 on success, else non-zero.
2310 */
2311static int
2312parse_fwd_field(char **p, struct fwdarg *fwd)
2313{
2314 char *ep, *cp = *p;
2315 int ispath = 0;
2316
2317 if (*cp == '\0') {
2318 *p = NULL;
2319 return -1; /* end of string */
2320 }
2321
2322 /*
2323 * A field escaped with square brackets is used literally.
2324 * XXX - allow ']' to be escaped via backslash?
2325 */
2326 if (*cp == '[') {
2327 /* find matching ']' */
2328 for (ep = cp + 1; *ep != ']' && *ep != '\0'; ep++) {
2329 if (*ep == '/')
2330 ispath = 1;
2331 }
2332 /* no matching ']' or not at end of field. */
2333 if (ep[0] != ']' || (ep[1] != ':' && ep[1] != '\0'))
2334 return -1;
2335 /* NUL terminate the field and advance p past the colon */
2336 *ep++ = '\0';
2337 if (*ep != '\0')
2338 *ep++ = '\0';
2339 fwd->arg = cp + 1;
2340 fwd->ispath = ispath;
2341 *p = ep;
2342 return 0;
2343 }
2344
2345 for (cp = *p; *cp != '\0'; cp++) {
2346 switch (*cp) {
2347 case '\\':
2348 memmove(cp, cp + 1, strlen(cp + 1) + 1);
2349 if (*cp == '\0')
2350 return -1;
2351 break;
2352 case '/':
2353 ispath = 1;
2354 break;
2355 case ':':
2356 *cp++ = '\0';
2357 goto done;
2358 }
2359 }
2360done:
2361 fwd->arg = *p;
2362 fwd->ispath = ispath;
2363 *p = cp;
2364 return 0;
2365}
2366
2367/*
2368 * parse_forward
2369 * parses a string containing a port forwarding specification of the form:
2370 * dynamicfwd == 0
2371 * [listenhost:]listenport|listenpath:connecthost:connectport|connectpath
2372 * listenpath:connectpath
2373 * dynamicfwd == 1
2374 * [listenhost:]listenport
2375 * returns number of arguments parsed or zero on error
2376 */
2377int
2378parse_forward(struct Forward *fwd, const char *fwdspec, int dynamicfwd, int remotefwd)
2379{
2380 struct fwdarg fwdargs[4];
2381 char *p, *cp;
2382 int i;
2383
2384 memset(fwd, 0, sizeof(*fwd));
2385 memset(fwdargs, 0, sizeof(fwdargs));
2386
2387 cp = p = xstrdup(fwdspec);
2388
2389 /* skip leading spaces */
2390 while (isspace((u_char)*cp))
2391 cp++;
2392
2393 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
2394 if (parse_fwd_field(&cp, &fwdargs[i]) != 0)
2395 break;
2396 }
2397
2398 /* Check for trailing garbage */
2399 if (cp != NULL && *cp != '\0') {
2400 i = 0; /* failure */
2401 }
2402
2403 switch (i) {
2404 case 1:
2405 if (fwdargs[0].ispath) {
2406 fwd->listen_path = xstrdup(fwdargs[0].arg);
2407 fwd->listen_port = PORT_STREAMLOCAL;
2408 } else {
2409 fwd->listen_host = NULL;
2410 fwd->listen_port = a2port(fwdargs[0].arg);
2411 }
2412 fwd->connect_host = xstrdup("socks");
2413 break;
2414
2415 case 2:
2416 if (fwdargs[0].ispath && fwdargs[1].ispath) {
2417 fwd->listen_path = xstrdup(fwdargs[0].arg);
2418 fwd->listen_port = PORT_STREAMLOCAL;
2419 fwd->connect_path = xstrdup(fwdargs[1].arg);
2420 fwd->connect_port = PORT_STREAMLOCAL;
2421 } else if (fwdargs[1].ispath) {
2422 fwd->listen_host = NULL;
2423 fwd->listen_port = a2port(fwdargs[0].arg);
2424 fwd->connect_path = xstrdup(fwdargs[1].arg);
2425 fwd->connect_port = PORT_STREAMLOCAL;
2426 } else {
2427 fwd->listen_host = xstrdup(fwdargs[0].arg);
2428 fwd->listen_port = a2port(fwdargs[1].arg);
2429 fwd->connect_host = xstrdup("socks");
2430 }
2431 break;
2432
2433 case 3:
2434 if (fwdargs[0].ispath) {
2435 fwd->listen_path = xstrdup(fwdargs[0].arg);
2436 fwd->listen_port = PORT_STREAMLOCAL;
2437 fwd->connect_host = xstrdup(fwdargs[1].arg);
2438 fwd->connect_port = a2port(fwdargs[2].arg);
2439 } else if (fwdargs[2].ispath) {
2440 fwd->listen_host = xstrdup(fwdargs[0].arg);
2441 fwd->listen_port = a2port(fwdargs[1].arg);
2442 fwd->connect_path = xstrdup(fwdargs[2].arg);
2443 fwd->connect_port = PORT_STREAMLOCAL;
2444 } else {
2445 fwd->listen_host = NULL;
2446 fwd->listen_port = a2port(fwdargs[0].arg);
2447 fwd->connect_host = xstrdup(fwdargs[1].arg);
2448 fwd->connect_port = a2port(fwdargs[2].arg);
2449 }
2450 break;
2451
2452 case 4:
2453 fwd->listen_host = xstrdup(fwdargs[0].arg);
2454 fwd->listen_port = a2port(fwdargs[1].arg);
2455 fwd->connect_host = xstrdup(fwdargs[2].arg);
2456 fwd->connect_port = a2port(fwdargs[3].arg);
2457 break;
2458 default:
2459 i = 0; /* failure */
2460 }
2461
2462 free(p);
2463
2464 if (dynamicfwd) {
2465 if (!(i == 1 || i == 2))
2466 goto fail_free;
2467 } else {
2468 if (!(i == 3 || i == 4)) {
2469 if (fwd->connect_path == NULL &&
2470 fwd->listen_path == NULL)
2471 goto fail_free;
2472 }
2473 if (fwd->connect_port <= 0 && fwd->connect_path == NULL)
2474 goto fail_free;
2475 }
2476
2477 if ((fwd->listen_port < 0 && fwd->listen_path == NULL) ||
2478 (!remotefwd && fwd->listen_port == 0))
2479 goto fail_free;
2480 if (fwd->connect_host != NULL &&
2481 strlen(fwd->connect_host) >= NI_MAXHOST)
2482 goto fail_free;
2483 /* XXX - if connecting to a remote socket, max sun len may not match this host */
2484 if (fwd->connect_path != NULL &&
2485 strlen(fwd->connect_path) >= PATH_MAX_SUN)
2486 goto fail_free;
2487 if (fwd->listen_host != NULL &&
2488 strlen(fwd->listen_host) >= NI_MAXHOST)
2489 goto fail_free;
2490 if (fwd->listen_path != NULL &&
2491 strlen(fwd->listen_path) >= PATH_MAX_SUN)
2492 goto fail_free;
2493
2494 return (i);
2495
2496 fail_free:
2497 free(fwd->connect_host);
2498 fwd->connect_host = NULL;
2499 free(fwd->connect_path);
2500 fwd->connect_path = NULL;
2501 free(fwd->listen_host);
2502 fwd->listen_host = NULL;
2503 free(fwd->listen_path);
2504 fwd->listen_path = NULL;
2505 return (0);
2506}

2508int
2509parse_jump(const char *s, Options *o, int active)
2510{
2511 char *orig, *sdup, *cp;
2512 char *host = NULL, *user = NULL;
2513 int ret = -1, port = -1, first;
2514
2515 active &= o->proxy_command == NULL && o->jump_host == NULL;
2516
2517 orig = sdup = xstrdup(s);
2518 first = active;
2519 do {
2520 if (strcasecmp(s, "none") == 0)
2521 break;
2522 if ((cp = strrchr(sdup, ',')) == NULL)
2523 cp = sdup; /* last */
2524 else
2525 *cp++ = '\0';
2526
2527 if (first) {
2528 /* First argument and configuration is active */
2529 if (parse_ssh_uri(cp, &user, &host, &port) == -1 ||
2530 parse_user_host_port(cp, &user, &host, &port) != 0)
2531 goto out;
2532 } else {
2533 /* Subsequent argument or inactive configuration */
2534 if (parse_ssh_uri(cp, NULL, NULL, NULL) == -1 ||
2535 parse_user_host_port(cp, NULL, NULL, NULL) != 0)
2536 goto out;
2537 }
2538 first = 0; /* only check syntax for subsequent hosts */
2539 } while (cp != sdup);
2540 /* success */
2541 if (active) {
2542 if (strcasecmp(s, "none") == 0) {
2543 o->jump_host = xstrdup("none");
2544 o->jump_port = 0;
2545 } else {
2546 o->jump_user = user;
2547 o->jump_host = host;
2548 o->jump_port = port;
2549 o->proxy_command = xstrdup("none");
2550 user = host = NULL;
2551 if ((cp = strrchr(s, ',')) != NULL && cp != s) {
2552 o->jump_extra = xstrdup(s);
2553 o->jump_extra[cp - s] = '\0';
2554 }
2555 }
2556 }
2557 ret = 0;
2558 out:
2559 free(orig);
2560 free(user);
2561 free(host);
2562 return ret;
2563}

2567{
2568 const char *path;
2569 int r;
2570
2571 r = parse_uri("ssh", uri, userp, hostp, portp, &path);
2572 if (r == 0 && path != NULL)
2573 r = -1; /* path not allowed */
2574 return r;
2575}

2630 u_int i;
2631
2632 for (i = 0; keywords[i].name != NULL; i++)
2633 if (keywords[i].opcode == code)
2634 return(keywords[i].name);
2635 return "UNKNOWN";
2636}

2639dump_cfg_int(OpCodes code, int val)
2640{
2641 printf("%s %d\n", lookup_opcode_name(code), val);
2642}

2645dump_cfg_fmtint(OpCodes code, int val)
2646{

2648}

2677
2678static void
2679dump_cfg_forwards(OpCodes code, u_int count, const struct Forward *fwds)
2680{
2681 const struct Forward *fwd;
2682 u_int i;
2683
2684 /* oDynamicForward */
2685 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
2686 fwd = &fwds[i];
2687 if (code == oDynamicForward && fwd->connect_host != NULL &&
2688 strcmp(fwd->connect_host, "socks") != 0)
2689 continue;
2690 if (code == oLocalForward && fwd->connect_host != NULL &&
2691 strcmp(fwd->connect_host, "socks") == 0)
2692 continue;
2693 printf("%s", lookup_opcode_name(code));
2694 if (fwd->listen_port == PORT_STREAMLOCAL)
2695 printf(" %s", fwd->listen_path);
2696 else if (fwd->listen_host == NULL)
2697 printf(" %d", fwd->listen_port);
2698 else {
2699 printf(" [%s]:%d",
2700 fwd->listen_host, fwd->listen_port);
2701 }
2702 if (code != oDynamicForward) {
2703 if (fwd->connect_port == PORT_STREAMLOCAL)
2704 printf(" %s", fwd->connect_path);
2705 else if (fwd->connect_host == NULL)
2706 printf(" %d", fwd->connect_port);
2707 else {
2708 printf(" [%s]:%d",
2709 fwd->connect_host, fwd->connect_port);
2710 }
2711 }
2712 printf("\n");
2713 }
2714}

2716void
2717dump_client_config(Options *o, const char *host)
2718{
2719 int i;
2720 char buf[8], *all_key;
2721
2722 /* This is normally prepared in ssh_kex2 */
2723 all_key = sshkey_alg_list(0, 0, 1, ',');
2724 if (kex_assemble_names( &o->hostkeyalgorithms,
2725 KEX_DEFAULT_PK_ALG, all_key) != 0)
2726 fatal("%s: kex_assemble_names failed", __func__);
2727 free(all_key);
2728
2729 /* Most interesting options first: user, host, port */
2730 dump_cfg_string(oUser, o->user);
2731 dump_cfg_string(oHostName, host);
2732 dump_cfg_int(oPort, o->port);
2733
2734 /* Flag options */
2735 dump_cfg_fmtint(oAddKeysToAgent, o->add_keys_to_agent);
2736 dump_cfg_fmtint(oAddressFamily, o->address_family);
2737 dump_cfg_fmtint(oBatchMode, o->batch_mode);
2738 dump_cfg_fmtint(oCanonicalizeFallbackLocal, o->canonicalize_fallback_local);
2739 dump_cfg_fmtint(oCanonicalizeHostname, o->canonicalize_hostname);
2740 dump_cfg_fmtint(oChallengeResponseAuthentication, o->challenge_response_authentication);
2741 dump_cfg_fmtint(oCheckHostIP, o->check_host_ip);
2742 dump_cfg_fmtint(oCompression, o->compression);
2743 dump_cfg_fmtint(oControlMaster, o->control_master);
2744 dump_cfg_fmtint(oEnableSSHKeysign, o->enable_ssh_keysign);
2745 dump_cfg_fmtint(oClearAllForwardings, o->clear_forwardings);
2746 dump_cfg_fmtint(oExitOnForwardFailure, o->exit_on_forward_failure);
2747 dump_cfg_fmtint(oFingerprintHash, o->fingerprint_hash);
2748 dump_cfg_fmtint(oForwardAgent, o->forward_agent);
2749 dump_cfg_fmtint(oForwardX11, o->forward_x11);
2750 dump_cfg_fmtint(oForwardX11Trusted, o->forward_x11_trusted);
2751 dump_cfg_fmtint(oGatewayPorts, o->fwd_opts.gateway_ports);
2752#ifdef GSSAPI
2753 dump_cfg_fmtint(oGssAuthentication, o->gss_authentication);
2754 dump_cfg_fmtint(oGssDelegateCreds, o->gss_deleg_creds);
2755#endif /* GSSAPI */
2756 dump_cfg_fmtint(oHashKnownHosts, o->hash_known_hosts);
2757 dump_cfg_fmtint(oHostbasedAuthentication, o->hostbased_authentication);
2758 dump_cfg_fmtint(oIdentitiesOnly, o->identities_only);
2759 dump_cfg_fmtint(oKbdInteractiveAuthentication, o->kbd_interactive_authentication);
2760 dump_cfg_fmtint(oNoHostAuthenticationForLocalhost, o->no_host_authentication_for_localhost);
2761 dump_cfg_fmtint(oPasswordAuthentication, o->password_authentication);
2762 dump_cfg_fmtint(oPermitLocalCommand, o->permit_local_command);
2763 dump_cfg_fmtint(oProxyUseFdpass, o->proxy_use_fdpass);
2764 dump_cfg_fmtint(oPubkeyAuthentication, o->pubkey_authentication);
2765 dump_cfg_fmtint(oRequestTTY, o->request_tty);
2766 dump_cfg_fmtint(oStreamLocalBindUnlink, o->fwd_opts.streamlocal_bind_unlink);
2767 dump_cfg_fmtint(oStrictHostKeyChecking, o->strict_host_key_checking);
2768 dump_cfg_fmtint(oTCPKeepAlive, o->tcp_keep_alive);
2769 dump_cfg_fmtint(oTunnel, o->tun_open);
2770 dump_cfg_fmtint(oVerifyHostKeyDNS, o->verify_host_key_dns);
2771 dump_cfg_fmtint(oVisualHostKey, o->visual_host_key);
2772 dump_cfg_fmtint(oUpdateHostkeys, o->update_hostkeys);
2773
2774 /* Integer options */
2775 dump_cfg_int(oCanonicalizeMaxDots, o->canonicalize_max_dots);
2776 dump_cfg_int(oConnectionAttempts, o->connection_attempts);
2777 dump_cfg_int(oForwardX11Timeout, o->forward_x11_timeout);
2778 dump_cfg_int(oNumberOfPasswordPrompts, o->number_of_password_prompts);
2779 dump_cfg_int(oServerAliveCountMax, o->server_alive_count_max);
2780 dump_cfg_int(oServerAliveInterval, o->server_alive_interval);
2781
2782 /* String options */
2783 dump_cfg_string(oBindAddress, o->bind_address);
2784 dump_cfg_string(oBindInterface, o->bind_interface);
2785 dump_cfg_string(oCiphers, o->ciphers ? o->ciphers : KEX_CLIENT_ENCRYPT);
2786 dump_cfg_string(oControlPath, o->control_path);
2787 dump_cfg_string(oHostKeyAlgorithms, o->hostkeyalgorithms);
2788 dump_cfg_string(oHostKeyAlias, o->host_key_alias);
2789 dump_cfg_string(oHostbasedKeyTypes, o->hostbased_key_types);
2790 dump_cfg_string(oIdentityAgent, o->identity_agent);
2791 dump_cfg_string(oIgnoreUnknown, o->ignored_unknown);
2792 dump_cfg_string(oKbdInteractiveDevices, o->kbd_interactive_devices);
2793 dump_cfg_string(oKexAlgorithms, o->kex_algorithms ? o->kex_algorithms : KEX_CLIENT_KEX);
2794 dump_cfg_string(oCASignatureAlgorithms, o->ca_sign_algorithms ? o->ca_sign_algorithms : SSH_ALLOWED_CA_SIGALGS);
2795 dump_cfg_string(oLocalCommand, o->local_command);
2796 dump_cfg_string(oRemoteCommand, o->remote_command);
2797 dump_cfg_string(oLogLevel, log_level_name(o->log_level));
2798 dump_cfg_string(oMacs, o->macs ? o->macs : KEX_CLIENT_MAC);
2799#ifdef ENABLE_PKCS11
2800 dump_cfg_string(oPKCS11Provider, o->pkcs11_provider);
2801#endif
2802 dump_cfg_string(oPreferredAuthentications, o->preferred_authentications);
2803 dump_cfg_string(oPubkeyAcceptedKeyTypes, o->pubkey_key_types);
2804 dump_cfg_string(oRevokedHostKeys, o->revoked_host_keys);
2805 dump_cfg_string(oXAuthLocation, o->xauth_location);
2806
2807 /* Forwards */
2808 dump_cfg_forwards(oDynamicForward, o->num_local_forwards, o->local_forwards);
2809 dump_cfg_forwards(oLocalForward, o->num_local_forwards, o->local_forwards);
2810 dump_cfg_forwards(oRemoteForward, o->num_remote_forwards, o->remote_forwards);
2811
2812 /* String array options */
2813 dump_cfg_strarray(oIdentityFile, o->num_identity_files, o->identity_files);
2814 dump_cfg_strarray_oneline(oCanonicalDomains, o->num_canonical_domains, o->canonical_domains);
2815 dump_cfg_strarray(oCertificateFile, o->num_certificate_files, o->certificate_files);
2816 dump_cfg_strarray_oneline(oGlobalKnownHostsFile, o->num_system_hostfiles, o->system_hostfiles);
2817 dump_cfg_strarray_oneline(oUserKnownHostsFile, o->num_user_hostfiles, o->user_hostfiles);
2818 dump_cfg_strarray(oSendEnv, o->num_send_env, o->send_env);
2819 dump_cfg_strarray(oSetEnv, o->num_setenv, o->setenv);
2820
2821 /* Special cases */
2822
2823 /* oConnectTimeout */
2824 if (o->connection_timeout == -1)
2825 printf("connecttimeout none\n");
2826 else
2827 dump_cfg_int(oConnectTimeout, o->connection_timeout);
2828
2829 /* oTunnelDevice */
2830 printf("tunneldevice");
2831 if (o->tun_local == SSH_TUNID_ANY)
2832 printf(" any");
2833 else
2834 printf(" %d", o->tun_local);
2835 if (o->tun_remote == SSH_TUNID_ANY)
2836 printf(":any");
2837 else
2838 printf(":%d", o->tun_remote);
2839 printf("\n");
2840
2841 /* oCanonicalizePermittedCNAMEs */
2842 if ( o->num_permitted_cnames > 0) {
2843 printf("canonicalizePermittedcnames");
2844 for (i = 0; i < o->num_permitted_cnames; i++) {
2845 printf(" %s:%s", o->permitted_cnames[i].source_list,
2846 o->permitted_cnames[i].target_list);
2847 }
2848 printf("\n");
2849 }
2850
2851 /* oControlPersist */
2852 if (o->control_persist == 0 || o->control_persist_timeout == 0)
2853 dump_cfg_fmtint(oControlPersist, o->control_persist);
2854 else
2855 dump_cfg_int(oControlPersist, o->control_persist_timeout);
2856
2857 /* oEscapeChar */
2858 if (o->escape_char == SSH_ESCAPECHAR_NONE)
2859 printf("escapechar none\n");
2860 else {
2861 vis(buf, o->escape_char, VIS_WHITE, 0);
2862 printf("escapechar %s\n", buf);
2863 }
2864
2865 /* oIPQoS */
2866 printf("ipqos %s ", iptos2str(o->ip_qos_interactive));
2867 printf("%s\n", iptos2str(o->ip_qos_bulk));
2868
2869 /* oRekeyLimit */
2870 printf("rekeylimit %llu %d\n",
2871 (unsigned long long)o->rekey_limit, o->rekey_interval);
2872
2873 /* oStreamLocalBindMask */
2874 printf("streamlocalbindmask 0%o\n",
2875 o->fwd_opts.streamlocal_bind_mask);
2876
2877 /* oLogFacility */
2878 printf("syslogfacility %s\n", log_facility_name(o->log_facility));
2879
2880 /* oProxyCommand / oProxyJump */
2881 if (o->jump_host == NULL)
2882 dump_cfg_string(oProxyCommand, o->proxy_command);
2883 else {
2884 /* Check for numeric addresses */
2885 i = strchr(o->jump_host, ':') != NULL ||
2886 strspn(o->jump_host, "1234567890.") == strlen(o->jump_host);
2887 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%d", o->jump_port);
2888 printf("proxyjump %s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s%s\n",
2889 /* optional additional jump spec */
2890 o->jump_extra == NULL ? "" : o->jump_extra,
2891 o->jump_extra == NULL ? "" : ",",
2892 /* optional user */
2893 o->jump_user == NULL ? "" : o->jump_user,
2894 o->jump_user == NULL ? "" : "@",
2895 /* opening [ if hostname is numeric */
2896 i ? "[" : "",
2897 /* mandatory hostname */
2898 o->jump_host,
2899 /* closing ] if hostname is numeric */
2900 i ? "]" : "",
2901 /* optional port number */
2902 o->jump_port <= 0 ? "" : ":",
2903 o->jump_port <= 0 ? "" : buf);
2904 }
